</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR57:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR57"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              57-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 57</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 68</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to Lexington and Concord Day. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">May 20, 2025.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 57, Patterson.
                          Lexington and Concord Day.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would recognize April 19, 2025, as Lexington and Concord Day.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_D117C406-8A3C-4504-8ED8-A4B6019BE3DA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, On the evening of April 18, 1775, Paul Revere and others riders alerted the countryside that British soldiers would be leaving Boston to confiscate and destroy stored arms in Concord and to arrest patriot leaders Sam Adams and John Hancock in Lexington; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E4658DA7-C89C-4256-B7A9-2D82676EB09E"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Local volunteers, mostly farmers and tradesmen organized into community militias and distinguished by the term “Minutemen,” answered the alarm and proceeded to Lexington and Concord to await the King’s soldiers; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0AD075C4-8D51-4C6B-8D1C-514C273EB3F9"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, At dawn on April 19, 1775, on the Lexington Green, over 700 British troops, known as “Redcoats,” approached the Green and ordered the 78 patriot volunteers gathered there to disperse; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_4DE3078A-5ACE-486F-8E6E-2997ED80D6CA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, A shot was fired,no one knows by who,that signaled the start of the war for American independence and came to be known as “The Shot Heard Around the World”; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_17CE4A45-359A-4CB5-AEDD-6B1CBA4CE292"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, British commanders lost control of their troops and, in the ensuing skirmish on Lexington Green, eight patriot volunteers were killed; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_5ED36071-0D24-416D-A883-4E1EE4FB6D86"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Redcoats continued their march to Concord, where about 400 American volunteers from local communities gathered throughout the morning; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_1E94728B-17B5-4434-86F9-A205DAC16FEF"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, A battle ensued at the Old North Bridge and the Redcoats were forced to quickly retreat to the center of town; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A0E06AE0-5096-4E35-B833-6555514DBC64"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Redcoats then began their march back to Boston under a constant stream of fire from the American volunteers; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_EB226E0A-0FBF-43CE-AACD-313D1C6CFA14"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Battles of Lexington and Concord marked the beginning of the American Revolution; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E95E3F29-963D-4C09-96E7-5A4D59F46AD5"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, April 19, 2025, marks the 250 year anniversary of the Battles of Lexington and Concord, the first battles in the American Revolution; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_77F63DF9-BCC0-48F4-8859-DD1BA055225C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature of the State of California recognizes April 19, 2025, as Lexington and Concord Day; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_634468A7-E992-4E7B-9FEF-E5C540243057"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
